A Crusaders tale, Journey of a life time<br>
  <br>
<br>
“Aye thanks for the room, I really appreciate the low price for this night, tis a stormy night it is.” <br>
“ Hehe, no problem Sir, you’re the only customer we have had in months. To come to think of it ever since the planes of power was opened I’m sure we would never get another customer.” <br>
The cloaked figure soaked in water unveiled his hood, as long black hair flown out all matted down. Seemingly he was muscular but not too beefy, soft face, with a black mustache. The figure kneeled down and gently grabbed the innkeepers hand and softly kissed it. <br>
“Greetings my lady, sorry I did not introduce myself to begin with my name is Magiith Mytherious, Crusader of Marr, avenger of justice.” <br>
The barkeeper blushed softly and giggled, as she handed The young crusader the key to his room.<br>
 “Hehe, ye can just called me Glenda, your room is right down the hall and the last one on the left.”<br>
<br>
 &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Magiith flirts a bit more then he gives Glenda a nod and walks off toward his room lugging several bags on his shoulder, leaving a small trail of water behind him. As soon as he entered the room, he lit a lantern up with a small gnomish device that looked like a stick, but as soon as you struck it on a rock it would burn with fire. He gave a glance around the room. Not the finest of all Inns, but he supposed it looked the most looked like a warm cozy place to settle in for the night. <br>
“Hmmm well, maybe I can see if I can mend this back together”<br>
Magiith was then fiddling with a thread and needle, feverously trying to patch a tear in his cloak. He was just almost done with the patch when the room suddenly filled with light and a huge crackling sound filled the Inn. <br>
 “Ow! What the… Stupid storm.” <br>
He then dropped the needle in surprise, a clank clink sound could be heard as it fell to the floor rolling under the bed.<br>
”Damn it, piece of crap, now I got to find that damn needle.”<br>
 &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
 &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The, well annoyed crusader then hoped off the bed and began a blind search for the needle.<br>
 “Hmm, well might I heard it roll under the bed might as well check there.” <br>
As he was searching under the bed he felt a piece of paper in the shape of a letter. He studied it, then as forgetting about the needle he got back up on the bed and lit another lantern.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> “Dear Lyrisii,<br>
Its mom if you ever get this letter, be known that I might never return back to our home in Sharvahl. As it turns out the West Freeport government is trying to hunt down our race for our fur… I don’t have much time now, They are trying to break down the Inn door, please if you get this letter know it that I love you… I will always, Take care of the litter for me. I don’t have much time left…<br>
 &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
Love, Melina Furrypaw.” </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
 Magiith, then suddenly felt a jolt of rage that such a horrible thing would be happening. He then bolted out of bed. He then put on all his body armor, then for the first time in 4 months, he unraveled a soft white cloth unveiling his blade, Times Scar.<br>
<br>
 &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp  This blade was his father’s he was a great warrior that journeyed to the plane of time and was the only one out of his party to make it back alive, and yet with such a treasure, Though his father was imprisoned inside the sword itself in a magic seal. from when an evil assassin Lothor snuck up upon his father in his sleep and stunned him by surprise. Teamed up with the wicked wizard Omiumbutu, They both were able to imprison his father directly inside the sword using an Ancient arcane curse. Though they both failed into stealing the legendary sword foraged in the planes of time, more or less made by the bare essence of the nameless. For that is what made it priceless and an object to desire. Of course by the time all this had happened my mother had woken up and used her spells that endowed the wrath of the gods to chase out the thieves… <br>
<br>
As magiith picked up the sword, he again felt the presence of his brave father, and gave him courage, as strength flowed though him… He then calmly walked out of the Inn into the stormy night heading toward Freeport with a disgusted and solemn look on his face… <br>
<br>
End, of the First chapter….<br>
